1
00:00:03,859 --> 00:00:08,215
We shouldn’t think that
voice of Guru, the order of Guru,

2
00:00:08,215 --> 00:00:10,748
the mantra of Guru, 
the instruction of Guru,

3
00:00:10,748 --> 00:00:13,337
is some sort of a static thing—

4
00:00:13,337 --> 00:00:17,018
“Oh, I was initiated twenty years ago, 
thirty years ago,

5
00:00:17,018 --> 00:00:20,071
forty years ago, any years ago”—

6
00:00:20,118 --> 00:00:23,306
[Dynamic Faith]

7
00:00:23,721 --> 00:00:27,800
but rather, Guru Mahārāj says,
“Vilasatu hrdi nityam bhakti”,

8
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:32,040
it’s eternally vibrating in our hearts—
the words, the message,

9
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:35,700
the order of Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur.

10
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:41,065
That’s what got Śrīla Prabhupād
to leave Vṛndāvan.

11
00:00:41,065 --> 00:00:43,347
I just spoke to Yudhamanyu Prabhu,
he was saying,

12
00:00:43,347 --> 00:00:47,514
“How old was Prabhupād?”
And we know he was something like

13
00:00:47,514 --> 00:00:56,517
69 years old when he boarded 
the Jaladuta ship

14
00:00:56,517 --> 00:00:58,716
to go from India to America,

15
00:00:58,716 --> 00:01:05,609
and these things cannot be accidental 
or coincidental.

16
00:01:05,609 --> 00:01:09,507
But Kṛṣṇa arranges things, 
he’s even kind to atheists,

17
00:01:09,507 --> 00:01:11,335
so if you want to disbelieve,

18
00:01:11,335 --> 00:01:13,563
He’s not going to disturb
your disbelief;

19
00:01:13,563 --> 00:01:20,934
He’ll give you all sorts of reasons, 
statistical analysis, to disbelieve.

20
00:01:20,934 --> 00:01:25,826
But faith cultures another thing too.

21
00:01:25,888 --> 00:01:30,209
So, Prabhupad … 
What is the name of the ship?

22
00:01:30,209 --> 00:01:35,824
The Jaladuta, which means
‘the water messenger’.

23
00:01:35,824 --> 00:01:40,111
And the diary they give—
they have a few; it’s a cargo ship

24
00:01:40,111 --> 00:01:45,320
and they give a few diaries to the passengers, 
it’s only a few passengers

25
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:48,067
and you have a little diary 
you can keep on the ship—

26
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:50,361
and Prabhupād would write things in it,

27
00:01:50,361 --> 00:01:53,660
and at the top, 
the running head of each page says,

28
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:58,512
“We carry India’s message 
of peace and good will.”

29
00:01:58,512 --> 00:02:02,424
So the ship called the Jaladuta, 
the water messenger,

30
00:02:02,424 --> 00:02:11,279
niṣṭhā śanti parāyaṇa, is carrying Prabhupād 
over the ocean to America

31
00:02:11,279 --> 00:02:16,468
to begin the world-wide inundation
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

32
00:02:17,298 --> 00:02:19,105
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

